The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Toyota Motor will increase its investment in India to about Rs 3,200 crore (68 billion yen) for its upcoming second plant in Bangalore. An additional amount of around 33 billion yen will be invested for both general purpose and specialised equipment necessary for manufacturing a new compact vehicle, the company said.                             
	 Aptech Ltd has posted a profit after tax of Rs 2.31 crore for the quarter ended September 30 against Rs 0.14 crore in the year-ago period. Income for the quarter under review grew to Rs 34.04 crore from Rs 27.32 crore a year ago.                             
	 TIL Ltd has posted a 50 per cent growth rate in total income for the second quarter ended September 30 at Rs 264.12 crore against Rs 176.44 crore in the year-ago period. The firms profit before tax rose to Rs 14.31 crore from Rs 9.34 crore a year ago.                             
	 Ramsarup Industries has posted a 44 per cent growth rate in total consolidated income for the quarter ended September 30 at Rs 478.59 crore against Rs 331.96 crore in the previous quarter. Operating profit grew 52 per cent to Rs 53.96 crore compared with Rs 35.61 crore a year ago.                            
	 Berger Paints India has registered a 21 per cent rise in sales at Rs 422.20 crore in the quarter ended September 30 against Rs 348.8 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal. Profit after tax grew 16.5 per cent to Rs 29.1 crore over the year-ago period.                             
	 Usha Martin Ltd has posted a growth rate of 13.9 per cent in consolidated profit after tax in the quarter ended September 30 at Rs 52.36 crore. Net sales for the quarter under review rose 39.7 per cent to Rs 806.36 crore.                             
	 Shree Cement has posted a 31 per cent rise in total income for the quarter ended September 30 at Rs Rs 647 crore against Rs 492 crore a year ago. The profit before interest, depreciation and taxes fell 6 per cent to Rs 216.35 crore from Rs 230.26 crore a year ago.                                                                                                                  ADVERTISEMENT                   
